text:
Hello！
Recently, Hanni’s Japanese has improved amazingly.
さいきん、ハニのにほんごのじょうたつにはおどろかされます。
Hanni said on a social networking site that you learned a little Japanese when you were in junior high school. 
ハニは、SNSでちゅうがくのときににほんごをすこしまなんだといってました。
You didn’t seem to learn much at the time.
そのときは、あまりみにつかなかったようですが
However, because of that learning, I think you must have the ability to grow your Japanese now.
でも、そのまなびがあったから、いまのにほんごのせいちょうりょくがあるのでしょう。
Ken 22:00 24/11/13 JPN

author: @boobinblur
text:
I love and deeply value the intimacy that Hanni's vlogs bring. They draw me in so uniquely, as if we were old friends, and each video feels like a personal message, a note from someone sharing their life sincerely. It’s comforting to watch the ease with which she navigates her world, the serene peace she radiates, and the genuine, simple love her family embodies. In each detail and small moment, it feels like I’m sharing the same memories with her, as if we’re writing the diary of her life together, page by page.

This touch of normalcy that Hanni gives us, with her natural beauty and captivating simplicity, creates a sense of connection that’s rare and precious. Hanni, please, never stop making these vlogs, especially with your family! They have become one of the warmest refuges I’ve found — like a hug in the form of a video. I’m immensely grateful to your parents, to Mom and Dad Pham, for raising such a sweet and generous person like you.

author: @cashilla
text:
Attention to what the haters or negatives are saying. Understand the members struggles and challenges, so you can provide encouragement that specifically addresses their needs. Acknowledge their efforts. Support NEW JEANS. Recognize the effort task or goal, regardless of the outcome. Appreciate how hard they’ve worked since day1.
Express words of encouragements show them and give all the members a generic praise, give them a specific compliment based on their abilities, strengths, or potential. Make them feel like you see them. Be genuine fan that supports them even in struggles and hard times but still doing their best for us fans. Authenticity matters. When you encourage someone or praise their efforts, say something you really mean, instead of saying something for the sake of it. Focus on the positive and stay strong Minji, Hanni, Danielle, Haerin, Hyein.
